review_blob: A: Golden, pretty cloudy. Very foamy but head is weak. S: Lots of citrus, Belgian yeast. Notes of spices. T: More lemon, I guess ginger sweetness, some hops on back of the tongue. Sweetish aftertaste with strong yeasty overtones. M: Quite dense for saison. O: Saison fever reached Finland.
A: Dark amber, slightly cloudy. S: Clear citrus, a bit of pine. T: Some malt, hoppy, citrusy. M: Pretty general IPA. O: Decent IPA, heavy Amarillo.
A: Brown, cloudy. Coffee foam small head. S: Caramel malt. T: Very bitter. Some liquorice, a bit of grass. Not much of dry hopping, mostly plain bitterness. M: Full. O: Alright.

A: Light amber, cloudy. Lots of head. S: Acidity, barnyard funk, some malt. T: Watery, with some funkiness. M: Very thin. O: Very thin and Brett ate too much. Saison from same brewery is a better sour.
A: Amber cloudy. S: Maracuya, tropical fruits, citrus. T: Citrus, tropical fruits, some acidity, tint of malt. M: Very refreshing. O: A very tropical ipa.
A: Amber, cloudy. S: Some barnyard, lactic acid. T: Starts sweet malt, tint of funk, tint of acidity, long mild barnyard aftertaste. M: Dry. O: OMG, awesome.
A: Red brown, some haze, some head. S: Some smoke, caramel malt, liquorice. T: Some malt, hint of liquorice, quite a lot of bitterness. M: Oily, quite heavy. O: Very decent APA, a bit heavy.
A: Straw golden, cloudy. Small head. S: Citrus, fruits, yeast. T: Some malt, lots of spice, some bitterness in aftertaste. M: Very light and sparkly. O: Great saison!

A: Amber, cloudy, small head. S: Lots of pine. T: Sweetish, grassy. Hop bitterness in the middle, ends with more grass. M: Pretty light, refreshing. O: Decent, balanced IPA, a bit too much dry hopping.
A: Amber, cloudy, solid head. S: Caramel malt, very slight hop raise. T: Malts, liquorice then pretty overwhelming bitterness. M: Medium. O: Very bitter beer. No other signs of IPA in smell or taste.
A: Golden, transparent. Weak head. S: Lager smell, some notes of alcohol. T: Some malt, lager taste. Ends bitter. M: Light lager. O: Better than your typical Finnish lager.
A: Amber slightly hazy. S: Malt, some lager smell. T: Starts sweet, some European bitterness, some sulfur, some very mild acidity. Some toasted malt. Finishes malt. M: Light. O: Not bad.

A: Amber brown, cloudy. Fast head. S: Lager smell, nothing more. T: Some light malts, fruitiness and a hint of acidity. Acidic and fruity aftertaste. M: Medium to light. O: Lager with some depth in taste, not too much.

A: Pitch black, creamy cocoa colored head. S: Chocolate, coffee, vanilla. T: Starts soft, with malt, liquorice, dark chocolate. Some hop bitterness. Ends bitter, with booze and warmth. M: Silky and creamy. O: Beer chocolate cake.
A: Golden, a bit cloudy, small head. S: Citrus, fruits. Some pine. T: Starts malts, goes into hop bitterness and nice rye spice and hop bitterness at the end. M: Pretty thin. O: Nice.
A: Straw, cloudy. S: Some earthy notes. T: Starts malt, bitterness, goes into deep earthiness. M: Pretty light. O: German hopped beer.

A: Amber, transparent. S: Some mild malt, earthy hops. T: Malts start, some very mild bitterness, ends sweetish with some hops. M: Quite light. O: A very British beer, hops are hard to taste after all the IPA.
A: Dark amber, cloudy. S: Fruit. T: Malts, liquorice, bitterness. M: Medium. O: Hoppy brown ale.
A: Dark amber, cloudy. Small head. S: Mango, pine. Malt. T: Explosive fruit taste, some liquorice, some mango. Cuts to bitterness, ends with little booze. M: Medium. O: Pacific IPA.

A: Dark amber, cloudy. S: Citrus, herbal, some booze like, maybe dark plum. T: Starts malt, goes to some hop bitterness, liquorice. Ends liquorice and bitterness. M: Quite solid. O: Solid, not overly IPAish.

A: Golden transparent. S: Winy, booze, some hops. T: Starts with malt, liquorice, some bitterness. Ends with some bitterness and alcohol warmth. M: Not so thick considering the abv. O: Not overly IPAish.

A: Golden, cloudy. Small head, pretty persistent. S: Citrusy, earthy. Very assertive European hops. T: Starts malt, then comes hops. There is bitterness and a lot of it and it sticks, but there is also a very assertive musky earth. M: Bodied enough. O: An IPA that tastes different!
A: Dark golden, cloudy. Weak head. S: Pine, hops. T: Some malts, goes very piny, herbal and grassy. Mildly bitter. Finishes mixed malt and bitterness. M: Relatively big. O: Very balanced IPA.

A: Golden cloudy. Loads of carbonation, strong thick head. S: Citrus, pepper. T: Pepper, spice, ends with some bitterness at the end. M: Quite watery, tingly carbonation. O: Surprisingly alright saison.

A: Red amber, transparent. S: Pine, tints of other hop aromas. T: After very short malt start, some herbs, grass, bitterness. Ends very bitter, with some liquorice at the end. M: Medium to deep. O: Decent American IPA.

A: Deep brown, on a level of Porter. S: Dark fruits, roasted malt, tint of booze, chocolate. T: Beginning is very dubbel like, sweetness, some dark fruit. Its much heavier on malt though, with liquorice, bitter roast. Finishes with lingering liquorice and dark malt. M: Pretty thick. O: Think dubbel thats been mixed with brown ale. This beet no overwhelming sweetness, but a very balanced snifter beer indeed.

A: Dark brown, cloudy, creamy head. S: Roasted malt, malt, liquorice. M: Mild sweetness, liquorice, some sourness, dark chocolate, most bitterness is dark malt based, but there are some hops. Bitter aftertaste. M: Creamy. O: Decent brown ale.

A: Very transparent light yellow. S: Slight malt, pilsner smell. T: Some malt notes, very small tint of bitterness in aftertaste. M: Quite light. O: Pretty straightforward cross between Finnish lager and Czech pilsner.

S: Strong spice, some citrus. A: Transparent without yeast, golden. Turns cloudy, a bit more yellow than normal wit. T: Some acidity, slight bitterness, spices. Some bitterness, some sweetness. M: Smooth. O: Good wit with saison feel.
A: Dark amber transparent. S: Malt, some smokiness. T: Some bitterswetness, fruits, coffee. Liquorice. M: Medium. O: Weird, not bad.
Slightly foggy, golden. S. Light maltiness, subtle fruits, pronounced English bitterness. Real ale watery. Ok.
A: Cloudy, golden. S: Some pine, citrus, tint of mango. T: Some hop bitterness, tint of sourness. M: Medium. O: Pretty straight forward IPA. No wit here.
A: Golden, cloudy. S: Strong pine, some malts. T: Some malts, then very strong German hop flavor. Ends bitter. M: Quite light. O: Hoppy Keller.
beer_name: Beer Here / Ugly Duck Helmuth Kellerbier

review_blob: A: Golden, cloudy, lacing. S: Malt, yeast. T: Very little sweetness up front, quickly becomes bitter, spice, tint of sourness and some sweetness at the end. M: Lively carbonated. O: Nice.
Tap at Black Door. A: Red, cloudy. S: Malts, molasses. Some subtle citrus. T: Very malty up front, some acidneed. Continues malty, no hops to be found. M: Very heavy. O: Too sweet.
A: Golden , transparent some head. S: Overripe Fruits, malt, sweetness. T: Some malt and more Fruits, goes into bitterness finishes bitter, lingers. Some honey tints. M: Medium. O: Alright.
A: Yellowish, as if wheat. S: Fruit, hop. T: Starts with light bitterness, goes into more bitterness. Some faint fruit. M: Watery and dry. O: Refreshing.

A: Dark yellow, cloudy. Head with some lacing. S: Citrus, lots of fruit, some acidity, hint of tartness. T: Starts moderately sweet, with tints of liquorice, caramelized fruits. Some spice, ends with very mild bitterness. M: Relatively sweet. O: Decent.

A: Black, with slight red hue. Almost no head. S: Coffee, caramel. M: Just a hint of sweetness, goes to mixed hop and coffee bitterness, some acidity and finishes with lingering coffee acid and caramel. M: There is a hint of oats, but I would expect a more silky/oily mouthfeel in an oatmeal stout. Pretty dry also. O: Alright.

A: Dark amber, cloudy, small white head. S: Some acid, some whiskey barell, malt, tint of herbs. T: Sweet liquorice, moves to bitterness, acid. Finishes with bitterness and alcohol warmth. M: Quite full. O: Pretty deep.
beer_name: Moon Dog Skunkworks Cognac Barrel Aged Double IPA

review_blob: A: Golden, some cloudness. Lots of carbonation, literally explodes when opened. S: Funk, barnyard. Some acidity. T: Spices, little sourness. Some residual hops. M: Watery. O: Very promising smell and very disappointing lack of taste.
A: Dark amber, small head, yellowish. S: Lots of dark fruit, caramel malt. T: Liquorice, some sweetness, bitter roast, alcohol warmth. M: Very smooth. O: Very deep.
A: Transparent golden, lacing foam. S: Suddenly cherry, yeast, citrus. T: Some subtle spice, acidity, residual sweetness. Dry at the end. O: Smell is remarkable. Very good.

A: Ale golden color, very transparent. Some white head. S: Subtle malt, some hop aroma. T: Starts a bit bland, there is a tint of sourness, some hops, some residual bitterness. M: Very light. O: Lager like Ale, reminds me of Kolsch.
A: Bright red transparent, small head. S: Cherry, fruit. T: Starts sour, goes to sweet raspberry and berry that persists. Lactic and sweet finish. M: Fizzy and pleasant. Dry. O: Excellent.

A: Dark amber, lively Belgian carbonation cloudy. S: Lactic acid, some funk, light barnyard. T: Sweetish start, some hop bitterness. Almost no funk in taste, hints of acid. Bitter Finish. M: Medium highly carbonated. O: Very nice.

A: Ale amber, transparent, small head. S: Strong raw malt. T: Trace malts, goes into bitterness, some dark fruit tanginess, long fruity and hopsy finish. M: Medium. O: Decent ale, bit on malty smell. Some decent taste overtones.

A: Cloudy yellow, typical weizen. S: Slightly funky weird smell, some wheat esters. T: Some banana, quickly gets masked by hops, pleasant bitterness. M: Light with carbonation. O: Very nice, I like combination of wheat and hops.
A: Cloudy yellow, small head. S: Mild hops, a little bit of malt. T: Starts sweet, some hops. Lingering bitterness. M: Light to medium. O: Alright session pale ale.

A: Dark brown, almost black. Lacing head. S: Citrus, yeast, strong malt. T: Starts sweet with liquorice overtones, goes into some dark fruit sweetness. Bitter aftertaste with some residual sweetness. M: Reasonably carbonated, light. O: Pretty decent, sweetness is not overwhelming.
